data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The signature changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Action<...>`, so manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code won't compile — but can now be dramatically simplified as shown.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** If both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will append a number to disambiguate (e.g., `Street1`). A migration will be generated renaming columns.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin to the old shorter name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Update your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the same parameter to every other method in the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
